Task 
Count the number of NaN values in an array

Write a function countNaN that takes the array arr as an argument and returns the number of elements in the array that are NaN.
Examples:
• the function countNaN ([NaN, 1, NaN + 1, "a" * 2]) must return 3, since this array contains three elements with the value NaN;
• the countNaN (['hello', 'Hello' * 5]) function must return 1;
• the countNaN ([NaN + 1]) function must return 1;
• the countNaN ([1, 2]) function must return 0;
• the countNaN ([]) function must return 0.

Solution
function countNaN(arr){
 let sum = 0 ;
 for(let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++){
  if (Number.isNaN(arr[i]) === true)
  sum ++;
 }
return sum;
}
